      "title": "Identify what the question needs",
      "content": "Find which ordered pair (x, y) satisfies both y = 4x + 11 and y = 4x^2 + 11 simultaneously. Substitute each choice into both equations."
    },
    {
      "title": "Eliminate the choices",
      "content": "<ul><li><strong>Choice A — $(0,0)$</strong>: $y = 4(0) + 11 = 11 \\ne 0$. &#10007;</li><li><strong>Choice B — $(0,11)$</strong>: $y = 4(0) + 11 = 11$ &#10003; and $y = 4(0)^2 + 11 = 11$ &#10003;. Both equations hold. &#10003;</li><li><strong>Choice C — $(22,99)$</strong>: $y = 4(22) + 11 = 99$ &#10003; but $y = 4(22)^2 + 11 = 1947 \\ne 99$. &#10007;</li><li><strong>Choice D — $(22,121)$</strong>: $y = 4(22) + 11 = 99 \\ne 121$. &#10007;</li></ul><strong>B</strong> is correct."
